  "source": "tips",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "tip — Paper 1 — Listening: pronouns and negatives in context",
  "reading": "Listen for whether the object pronoun is ‘lo/la’ (singular) or ‘los/las’ (plural), and for the negative word right after ‘no’ — ‘nada’, ‘nunca’ or ‘nadie’ completely change the meaning even though they sound similar.",
  "question": "You hear ‘no … nadie’. What does that tell you?",
